data.enText: a level on a scale, often marking quality or achievement
The quality of the food here has dropped a notch recently.
data.chText: 这里的饭菜质量最近下降了一级。

data.enText: a V-shape or a circle cut in an edge or a surface, sometimes used to keep a record of sth
data.chText: （表面或边缘的）V形刻痕，圆形切口

data.enText: For each day he spent on the island, he cut a new notch in his stick.
data.chText: 他在岛上每过一天，就在手杖上刻一个新的记号。

data.enText: She tightened her belt an extra notch.
data.chText: 她将腰带又束紧了一格。

data.enText: to achieve sth such as a win or a high score
The team has notched up 20 goals already this season.
data.chText: 这支球队本赛季已经攻进20个球。

data.enText: to make a small V-shaped cut in an edge or a surface
data.chText: （在表面或边缘）刻V形痕，刻下切口

means: (表面或边缘的)V形刻痕，圆形切口
(在表面或边缘)刻V形痕，刻下切口

tr: a V-shaped or U-shaped indentation carved or scratched into a surface
example: there were four notches in the handle of his revolver

tr: the location in a range of mountains of a geological formation that is lower than the surrounding peaks
example: we got through the pass before it started to snow

tr: notch a surface to record something
cut or make a notch into

example.ex: Average earnings in the economy moved up another notch in August...
example.tran: 8月份这个国家的平均收入又上了一个台阶。

example.ex: In this country the good players are pulled down a notch or two...
example.tran: 在这个国家，优秀选手的水平降了一两个档次。

example.ex: On the third day, General Zhang raised the temperature of the assembly a few notches.
example.tran: 第三天，张将军使大会的热烈程度提高了几档。

value.def: You can refer to a level on a scale of measurement or achievement as a notch .

example.ex: Steve Bull notched his 200th goal for Wolves as they beat Leicester 3-0...
example.tran: 史蒂夫·布尔为狼队攻入了他的第200粒进球，他们以3比0击败了莱斯特队。

example.ex: The President is keen to notch a political triumph that would foster freer world trade and faster economic growth.
example.tran: 总统渴望获得政治胜利，以促使世界贸易更为自由，经济发展更为迅速。

value.def: If you notch a success, especially in a sporting contest, you achieve it.

example.ex: They cut notches in the handle of their pistol for each man they shot.
example.tran: 他们每杀一个人就在枪托上刻下一个V形记号。

value.def: A notch is a small V-shaped or circular cut in the surface or edge of something.
